post_text: Scottsbluff Educators Rising is excited to announce that senior member Gabriela Aguilar will be featured on Nebraska's Teacher TV. Gaby volunteered to teach a lesson entitled "Mi Vida Nueva". During her lesson, she will read a book written and illustrated by Gaby and Taylor Klein. Their book, "Mi Vida Nueva" placed third at the Nebraska Educators Rising State Conference and qualified for the National Convention in 2018. Gaby's lesson will air Tuesday, May 5th on Telemundo, and can be viewed live or on demand on Telemundo Nebraska or https://ecs.page.link/qA6Jm

shared_text:
Scottsbluff High School Musical Theatre Productions
April 27 at 11:56 PM ¬∑

Update: We are still in a holding pattern, waiting to see if a summer production (live or streamed) would be possible. The performers have been ANXIOUSLY waiting for news as well. We won't know more for a few weeks still.

Here's the scoop on tickets:
1) We will honor all purchased tickets if we are able to do the show this summer.
2) If the show is cancelled altogether, we will offer refunds. Many people have already said the don't want their money refunded.
3) If you wish to get a refund before that time, please email Mr. Ronne: (bronne@sbps.net)

Thank you!
